%I A396142 #6 May 21 2026 23:30:00
%S A396142 1,1,1,2,5,9,20,42,87,199,443,1036,2425,5860,14093,34662,85147,211553,
%T A396142 526163,1317021,3301812,8310109,20949432,52950667,134043902
%N A396142 Number of endless undirected self-avoiding paths in the square lattice, comprised of a repeating primitive path of length n, with rotations, reflections, and translations not counted as distinct.
%C A396142 Here a primitive path is one which is not a repetition of a smaller path or congruent to a smaller path.
%C A396142 Equals A334398 excluding nonprimitive cases and cases that are redundant due to congruence. See Example.
%C A396142 Equals A396017 including only cases that can repeat to form an endless self-avoiding path.
%e A396142 a(6) = 9 (with uppercase letters denoting positive direction steps in XY coordinates and lowercase denoting negative steps, each repeated to form an endless path): XXXXXY, XXXYxY, XXXYXy, XXXYXY, XXYxxY, XXYXXy, XXYXyy, XXYXYY, and XYXYXy.
%e A396142 Examples of paths not counted for n = 6: XXYXXY (repetition of primitive path XXY, counted for n = 3), XXXYYY (congruent to primitive path XY, counted for n = 2), XXXXYX (endless path is congruent to that of XXXXXY), and XXXXYx: (endless path is self-intersecting).
%Y A396142 Cf. A334398, A396017.
%K A396142 nonn,walk,hard,more,new
%O A396142 1,4
%A A396142 _Charles L. Hohn_, May 18 2026
